title: 1973 Horror - The Death Wheelers - Ride with the Living Dead!

sources.title: 1973 Horror - The Death Wheelers - Ride with the Living Dead!
sources.description:
Tom Latham, a charming and unhinged leader of the rebellious biker gang "The Living Dead," is influenced by his mystic mother, a practitioner of dark arts, to take a dramatic leap into the unknown and return as "undead." Turning his crew into unstoppable chaos-makers who terrorize their English town, Tom’s wild ride spirals into a high-octane clash between life, death, and the ultimate price of power, with his loyal friend Abby caught in the crossfire.

Original title: Psychomania (1973)
Alternative title: The Death Wheelers

Director: Don Sharp
Writers: Arnaud d'Usseau, Julian Zimet

Main cast:
Nicky Henson - Tom Latham
Beryl Reid - Mrs. Latham
George Sanders - Shadwell
Mary Larkin - Abby Holman

Genres: Dark comedy, Horror, Supernatural, Bikersploitation
Release date: 1973
Filming location: Surrey, England


00:00 Full Movie with subtitles
02:44 Tom Latham and his biker gang, The Living Dead, create chaos in their English town.
13:22 Tom confronts his mother, Mrs. Latham, demanding the secret of returning from the dead, setting his supernatural quest in motion.
27:28 Tom, in a reckless act, rides his motorcycle off a bridge, sacrificing himself to prove his belief in resurrection.
41:43 Tom, now undead, calls Shadwell and Mrs. Latham, boasting about his return and unsettling the living with his presence.
46:26 Tom reclaims leadership of the gang, urging them to die and return like him, testing their faith and loyalty.
52:03 Abby discovers that Henky hesitated at the last moment and did not return, while Jane has become one of the dead.
69:22 Abby, revived after a near-death experience, is questioned by the inspector about the gang’s obsession with death.
1:22:34 Mrs. Latham seals her fate in a final occult ritual with Shadwell, accepting the eternal consequences for her and Tom.
